  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if a reduced intensity (RI) (non-myeloablative)
      chemoimmunotherapy followed by Allogeneic Stem Cell Transplantation AlloSCT (matched family
      donors and matched unrelated cord blood donors) will be well tolerated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is to test whether a reduced intensity will result in a high degree of mixed or complete
      donor chimerism and stabilization of autoimmune disease in a select group of patients with
      medically refractory SLE or SSc.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
